args: Torch it! Incinerate the rebels and\neverything they own!
The entire village is in flames...
You again?! When will you learn to\nmind your own business, traitor?!
How can you be so cruel?!
All who would oppose the great Dyrenell\nEmpire must receive purification!
This village refused us proper honors,\nso we set it to burn in a great cleansing!
You would dare sully the name of\n＂cleansing＂ by attaching it to such\ncowardly, wanton violence?!
We are men of the Divine Torch, and this\nis the sacred duty conferred upon us!
The Divine Torch?! Holy hell, yer them\nEmpire guys what wander the countryside\nsettin' fire to everybody's homes!

You seek to give your actions purpose,
yet you are naught but the most base
and cruel of brigands—and I will see
you pay for your deeds!
As if the Divine Torch could be felled\nby such a haphazard assault!\nTo arms, men! Slay them all!
Fjorm, stop! ...Dammit! We gotta go\nafter her, {player_name}.
Yeah, she'll never be able to take\non that many enemies by herself.
Burn everything!\nLet not even a mouse escape!
Gah, the flames! I can't...reach them!
The fire is too big for us to put out!\nWe have to prioritize getting the\nvillagers out of here!
Ranzal! Elisanne! Round up everyone\nyou can find and get them to safety!
Don't worry—we'll get 'em all outta here!
Please take care of Princess Fjorm,\nYour Highness!
All right, Fjorm. We're going to—
Wait, stop! Where are you going?!
There is no escape for you, heretic!
Urgh! I won't lose to you cravens! Haaah!
By Ilia, what a wound!\nI must treat that at once!
I'm fine. Just...get the boy to safety.
I will be fine. Now go! Hurry!
That's a really bad burn, Fjorm.
We have to go. It's not safe here.
Here Fjorm—hold on to my shoulder.
